In this article, President Trump and Senate Majority Leader McConnell discuss the importance of border security and the need for a barrier to stop human trafficking, drug trade, and gang activity. The President also mentions the possibility of declaring a national emergency if Chuck and Nancy, referring to Democratic leaders, do not agree to address the problems at the southern border. He emphasizes that the Republicans are unified in wanting border security and that the Democrats who oppose it may face political consequences. The President also highlights the decrease in illegal immigration due to good management but argues that a real barrier is necessary for effective control.